1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with the task of translating between programming languages, which involves understanding the syntax and structure of the source and target languages. This is a natural fit for the Computation and Language sub-category.
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a neural network model for program language translation, which is a common application of AI in the field of programming. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed model is a neural network that uses machine learning techniques to learn the mapping between source and target languages. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper deals with the task of translating between programming languages, which is a common problem in software engineering when integrating different systems or libraries. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper deals with the task of translating between programming languages, which is a core topic in the field of programming languages.
